<tool id="show_3D_surface_plot" name="show_3D_surface_plot" version="0.0.1">
  <description>Makes a surface plot from a 3D synthetic image.</description>
  <command interpreter="bash">
    show_3D_surface_plot.sh $input $viewanglex $viewangley $alphavalue
  </command>
  <inputs>
    <param format="zip" name="input" type="data" label="3D image"></param>
    <param name="viewanglex" type="integer" value="20" label="View angle on x-direction"/>
    <param name="viewangley" type="integer" value="-30" label="View angle on y-direction"/>
    <param name="alphavalue" type="float" value="0.1" label="alpha-value"/>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="png" name="output" from_work_dir="output.png"/>
  </outputs>
<help>

**Description**

Makes PNG file from a surface plot of a 3D synthetic image.

-----

**Input**

- 3D synthetic image

-----

**Output**

- A PNG file.
</help>
</tool>
